1.00	Transfer-matrix_method_(optics)	Transfer-matrix method (optics)	The transfer-matrix method is a method used in optics and acoustics to analyze the propagation of electromagnetic or acoustic waves through a stratified (layered) medium. This is for example relevant for the design of anti-reflective coatings and dielectric mirrors.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/db/Etalon-1.svg/220px-Etalon-1.svg.png
